						<summary><p>#6: a) Lakṣmīnārāyaṇa temple, Javantināthapuram, Lālkuṭi taluk, Trichy district; b) on a stone (perhaps was it a doorjamb originally?), embedded in the right-side cement pillar of the gate; c) Regnal year 9 opposite to 4 of Māṟañcaṭaiyaṉ, <foreign>aviṭṭa </foreign>day, which falls on Monday in the month of <foreign>dhanus</foreign>;40 d) are 1946–1947, no. 104; ei 28, no. 6; iep 41; e) inscription located personally; f) the last syllable of each line is not visible, even on the estampage published in 1940–1950 in ei 28, but can be easily guessed in most of the cases; I have restored them in the text in square brackets with an asterisk; the inscription stops abruptly, the remaining part of it perhaps covered by cement.</p>

</summary>
