<p>Hail! Prosperity! <supplied reason="subaudible">This is</supplied> the 9th year opposite to the 4th year of king Māṟañcaṭaiyaṉ; from <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>mutal āka</foreign></supplied> <foreign>aviṭṭa </foreign>obtained on Monday <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiṅkaṭ-kiḻamai</foreign></supplied> in the month of <foreign>dhanus</foreign>; for Perumāṉaṭikaḷ of Tirumayilaraṅkam in Iṭaiyyāṟṟu <foreign>maṅkalam</foreign>, night and day, for burning <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>erippatāka</foreign></supplied> two <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iraṇṭu</foreign></supplied> perpetual lamps, king <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kō</foreign></supplied> Māṟañcaṭaiyar <foreign>alias </foreign>Varaguṇa Mahārājar, the great Lord of the Pāṇḍyans, released and gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>viṭu-tanta</foreign></supplied> into the hand <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaiyyil</foreign></supplied> of Aṇṭanāṭṭu Vēḷāṉ, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> gold <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></p></div>

